# OneChoiceKitchen — Cursor Rules

## Project
Enterprise-grade food delivery platform. Nx monorepo with pnpm.

## Stack
- Frontend: Next.js 14 App Router (React Server Components)
- Backend: NestJS with Prisma ORM
- Database: PostgreSQL 15
- Cache/Queue: Redis + BullMQ
- Build: Nx workspace

## Workspace Layout
- apps/api/         → NestJS backend (port 3000)
- apps/web/         → Customer web app (port 4208)
- apps/admin/       → Admin portal (port 4205)
- apps/partner/     → Partner portal (port 4206)
- apps/rider/       → Rider portal (port 4207)
- libs/             → Shared code
- prisma/           → Schema + migrations + seeds

## Skills (read before any task)
All AI knowledge base lives in .agents/skills/
Load in order:
1. .agents/skills/project-context/SKILL.md
2. .agents/skills/onechoice-business-rules/SKILL.md
3. Task-specific skill

## Rules
- Package manager: pnpm ONLY (never npm/yarn)
- Tasks via: pnpm nx [task] [project]
- All new code needs tests (no skip)
- All API endpoints need JwtAuthGuard
- Monetary values: Decimal @db.Decimal(10,2) NEVER Float
- No any TypeScript type without justification
- No hardcoded secrets
